**POD**

1. kubectl create/apply -f pod.yaml          ---- to creat pod
2. kubectl get pods                          ---- to check all pod
3. kubectl get pod -o wide                   ---- to check where pod is running
4. kubectl decribe pod pod-name              ---- to check details of pods
5. kubectl delete pod pod-name               ---- to delete pod
6. kubectl logs -f pod-name                  ---- to check pod logs
7. kubectl get pods -n namespace-name        ---- to see pods on perticular namespace

      **NAMESPACE**
7. kubectl create -f namespace.yaml          ---- to create namespace
8. kubectl get namespace                     ---- to see available namespaces
9. kubectl describe namespace namespace-name ---- todescribe a namespace
10. kubectl create -f  deployment.yaml OR configmap.yaml OR secret.yaml OR service.yaml    ---- to creat all same comad used

